    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Preston</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-12-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 10, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram received. The American minister at Port au Prince has been fully
                    instructed to inform the provisional authorities there of the President’s
                    decision in the case of the <hi rend="italic">Haytien Republic</hi>, so that
                    nothing more will be necessary than compliance with that decision.</p>
                <p>The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Galena</hi> will sail from New York to-morrow
                    morning, and should you desire to avail yourself of the courtesy, the commander
                    will no doubt convey your communications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
